# iMessage Agent Environment Setup

To get your iMessage agent running, you need to set up a few environment variables. You can create a file named `.env` in the project root with the following content:

```bash
# Your Google Gemini API Key (Free Tier works)
# Get it here: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
export GEMINI_API_KEY='your_gemini_api_key_here'

# BlueBubbles Settings (Usually defaults are fine if running locally)
export BLUEBUBBLES_URL='http://localhost:1234'
export BLUEBUBBLES_PASSWORD='your_bluebubbles_password_here'

# Your iMessage Chat GUID (You can find this in BlueBubbles Server logs or UI)
# Usually looks like: iMessage;-;user@example.com
export IMESSAGE_CHAT_GUID='your_target_chat_guid_here'
```

### How to use:
1. Copy the above into a file named `.env`.
2. Run `source .env` in your terminal before starting the agent.
